.TH "hex2bin" 9 "hex2bin" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hex2bin \- convert an ascii hexadecimal string to its binary representation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hex2bin
.BI "(u8 *dst "  ","
.BI "const char *src "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
binary result
.IP "src" 12
ascii hexadecimal string
.IP "count" 12
result length
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 0 on success, -EINVAL in case of bad input.
